		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Look for the 7805, right leg, anything soldered to the trace from it or the leg itself. Grab a multimeter and start hunting...

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Xious</b> [ Sun Aug 29, 2010 4:20 am ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Pin 15 of the EXP port connector (on the side) is +5DVC.
<br />
<br />Here is my own handy-dandy pinout reference sheet:
<br />
<br />FC DA-15				NES 48-Pin DSub EXP
<br />1 – Ground			
<br />2 - Sound Output			
<br />3 – IRQ				
<br />4 - Port #1 (D4) 4017R.4		
<br />5 - Port #1 (D3) 4017R.3		
<br />6 - Port #1 (D2) 4017R.2		
<br />7 - Port #1 (D1) 4017R.1		
<br />8 - Port #1 (D0) 4017R.0		
<br />9 - Port #1 CLK 4017R.E		
<br />10 - Out2 4016WR.2		
<br />11 - Out1 4016WR.1		
<br />12 - Out0 4016WR.0		
<br />13 - Port #0 (D1) 4016R.1	
<br />14 - Port #0 CLK	4016R.E	
<br />15 - +5VDC

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


